description: Configure a medium type for connecting interlink ports for CXU board redundancy.
Setting the interlink to disabled means OSR (optical splitter redundancy),
while setting it to internal or SFP means ILR (interlink redundancy).
Only CXU_C, CXU_B and CXU_B1 support internal electrical interfaces (placed on board).
Therefor only for these card types a configuration of the used interlink type is possible.
All other CXU types could not be configured here and use value disabled(0).
In addition to the interlink type the standby laser configuration has to be changed accordingly.
In case of ILR, any configuration of interlinks is stored but not executed as the interlinks
are controlled by an interlink monitor instance.
The stored configuration of interlink is executed either after configuration to OSR or if the
The default value for legacy CXUs is enabled, while for nextGenCXUs it is disabled.

description: A given port's link status is monitored (link monitoring on if true).
When link down for the port is detected, switchover from an active board
to a standby board is performed.
With R3.8M additional parameters were introduced to configure linkweight (per port)
linkprobe (per port), thresholds (global) and switchover delays (global).
Link monitoring is only supported for redundancy concepts using an optical splitter or
directly connected uplinks (but not for interlink redundancy).
variables.name: SHE-ETHERNET-MIB::sheEthernetPortSwitchoverOnLinkDown

description: Each uplink port gets a certain weight for link monitoring.
The default value for the weight is the configured line speed divided by 1 Mbps.
i.e the 1GE line gets 1000, the 10GE line 10000
variables.name: SHE-ETHERNET-MIB::sheEthernetPortLinkMonitorWeight

description: Configures the probe handling of an uplink on standby CXU for link monitoring.
If probe is set to enabled the link on standby CXU is enabled during probe handling if
the corresponding link on active CXU is down.
If probe is set to disabled (default) the uplink port on standby CXU is not used for
If probe is set to force the uplink on standby CXU is used in probe handling regardless
on the corresponding active uplink's status.
variables.name: SHE-ETHERNET-MIB::sheEthernetPortLinkMonitorProbe

description: Time stamp attribute set at the end of a command.
variables.name: SHE-ETHERNET-MIB::sheEthernetPortControlTimestamp

description: The link monitor checks continuously the sum of the weights of the available and monitored uplink
ports against the sum of the weights of the monitored uplink ports.
If the first sum falls below a certain percentage of the second one, a CXU switchover is triggered
but only if the standby CXU is known in a better state.
This threshold shall be configured via this parameter.
The threshold is given in steps of 0.1 % and the default value is set to 999 -> 99,9%.
variables.name: SHE-ETHERNET-MIB::sheEthernetLinkMonitorThreshold

description: This parameter defines a possible switchover delay if the link monitor process detects a switchover
condition. The default setting is no delay (0).
variables.name: SHE-ETHERNET-MIB::sheEthernetLinkMonitorSwitchOverDelay
